news.title: Shriram Properties IPO subscribed 89% on day one
news.para: Shriram Properties on Tuesday said it has raised a little over Rs 268 crore from anchor investors ahead of its initial share-sale. The company decided to allocate 2,27,66,949 equity shares to anchor investors at Rs 118 apiece, valuing the transaction size to Rs 268.64 crore, according to a BSE circular.

news.title: Cabinet approves continuation of PMAY-Gramin till March 2024
news.para: The total financial implication for construction of the remaining 155.75 lakh houses is Rs. 2,17,257 crore or achieving cumulative targets of 2.95 crore houses in rural areas under the PMAY-Gramin.

news.title: Gujarat HC tells lawyers to inspect tallest building in Gandhinagar
news.para: ​Petitioner’s counsel Hardik Pandit submitted that the civic body did not take action against the developer J K Infrastructure because of involvement of ex-mayor Ritaben Patel.
